Pacific Dunlop Ltd said it will makea one-for-ten bonus issue from its asset revaluation reserve toshareholders registered June 15.    The bonus involves the issue of about 45 mln shares, thediversified rubber and plastics group said in a statement.    The new shares will not rank for the deferred annualdividend of not less than 12.5 cts that Pacific Dunlop will payin August, but will rank pari passu thereafter, it said.    As previously reported, it did not pay an interim dividendfor the first half to December 31 pending a review of the newdividend imputation legislation. REUTER&#3;